Linux Commands
---------------
Text-based instructions that you type into a terminal (command line) to the linux operating systems what to do

There are some specific commands based on distribution - ubuntu, centos

<commands are case sensitive - >

Navigate to system

pwd = present working directory 
ls = list files and folder in the 
ls -a  = To list all hidden files and folder
ls -l = long listing command
cd    = Move to specific directory </home>
cd ..  = Move one step back
cd ~   = Go to home directory

Create & Manage Files/Folder

mkdir <folder_name>   = Create a folder/directory  
touch <file_name>     = To Create a empty file
cp<file_name> <folder_name> = To copy the file to give folder
mv <old_file_name> <new_file_name> = To rename the file 